author: Cleo Abram
description:
One specific area of the US has been dubbed a “mummy zone” for dinosaurs. Scientists uncovered specimens that were stunningly preserved. 

They could count individual scales on the body, hooves, and a fleshy crest on the top. 

How could an animal that died 66 million years ago be preserved in such amazing detail? 

Subscribe to learn more!

DOI: 10.1126/science.adw3536
